keyFacts: The document contains confidential Citibank account records from evidence gathered by the Southern District of New York (SDNY_GM series).
Multiple accounts are listed for entities named 'SLR DESIGNS' and 'SIX DESIGNS LLC', with opening dates ranging from 2001 to 2012.
All accounts shown are marked as 'Very Important Business (VIB)' and 'Not for Automatic Verification', suggesting they were subject to special handling or scrutiny.
Each account record includes a 'Fraud Indicator' and 'Fraud Years' field, indicating these accounts were part of a financial investigation.
The document identifiers (EFTA01265301-EFTA01265312) suggest it is part of a larger set of financial transaction records related to the case.
